summary: Intimidated by ENBseries? Want to make your game look better? Oh, do I have something for you! This package contains a labelled configuration file and tweaked settings for ENBseries (v0.102/3)! Aww yeah!
descriptionHtml:
[center][img]http://static.skyrimnexus.com/downloads/images/4434-1-1324660199.png[/img]
One of several hundred![/center]

Intimidated by ENBseries? Want to make your game look better? Oh, do I have something for you! 

This file will, through the strange and arcane magicks of ENBseries, change the way your Skyrim looks! For some, it may be better! For others, it may be worse. 
But wait, that\'s not all! It also contains labels for the settings in enbseries.ini! I\'ve gone through and tried to provide easy-to-understand descriptions for the various things you can tweak.

Featuring... [list][*]Descriptive labels for most options in the configuration
[*]Vivid colours with saturated days, nights, and almost everything else
[*]SSAO enabled!
[*]Helpful instructions on how to turn SSAO off
[*]Tweaked lighting settings!
[*]Insert buzzword here
[*]Kinda realistic, but not really
[*]Shiny specular lighting for more defined detail
[*]Slight blue shifting to provide better colour balance
[*]Lens reflection effects - gives depth to your screen!
[*]Immersive in some particularily obscure and arcane way
[*]Indirect lighting for maximum graphical enjoyification
[*]Altered fog to provide both realism and graphical shininess[/list]

Naturally, to use this mod, you\'ll need [url=http://skyrimnexus.com/downloads/file.php?id=2971]the original ENBseries mod to begin with[/url]. Then just place this one over it! For more information, read the readme. 

This mod was developed with an [b]i5[/b] CPU, and a [b]GTX 460 SE[/b], using [s]SkyBoost[/s] patch 1.4. If you don\'t have a computer that matches up to these settings, you\'ll probably want to check the readme for performance boosting tips. 

Right now, this is at version two. There are several settings without in-depth explanations of how they work. Any help constructing better descriptors would be much appreciated!
